<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued July 03 at 12:57PM MDT until July 03 at 8:00PM MDT by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...THE SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING FOR SOUTH CENTRAL BEAVERHEAD
COUNTY WILL EXPIRE AT 100 PM MDT...
The storm which prompted the warning has moved further to the east.
A new Severe Thunderstorm Warning has been posted.
A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 PM MDT for
southwestern Montana.
Remember, a Severe Thunderstorm Warning still remains in effect for
South Central Beaverhead County until 200 PM MDT.</description>
